        "text": "In the case of [[directed graph]]s, arrowheads ([[Arrow (symbol)]]) form a commonly used graphical convention to show their orientation ([[Orientability]]);<ref name=\"dett6\"/> however, user studies have shown that other conventions such as tapering provide this information more effectively. [[Upward planar drawing]] uses the convention that every edge is oriented from a lower vertex to a higher vertex, making arrowheads unnecessary."
